@node Description "Description of DiceCalc."

DESCRIPTION

    Dice Calculator is a program similar to a normal calculator, but instead
it generates a random number. The formula used should be familiar to most role
players. For example a 6 sided die will give a number between 1 and 6 and is
represented by 1d6. The 1 is the number of rolls, and the 6 is the number of
sides.
    You can also add (or subtract) what is known as a modifier. After the die
has been rolled the specified number of times, a final number is rolled.

ie. 2d6+2 will give a final number between 4 and 14
    5d10-5 will give a final number between 0 and 45

The possiblities are endless.

I've set the maximum number of rolls to 999 and the maximum modifier to 9999. If
you decide that these aren't big enough then send me a message somehow, and
I'll compile you your own personalized version.


@endnode

@node usage "How to use it!"

USAGE

    from a cli:     Dicecalc    (no options)
    from Workbench:  double click icon.  (no tooltypes yet)

A short description of each key follows.

Roll - (Return key) Will roll the die and display the result.
Clear - (Delete key) Clears the display and sets number of rolls and modifier
        to zero
About - Some info on the program.
Help key - All programs should use the help key!! This should help you?
Number pad - (any number key) Enter either number of rolls or the modifier.
Plus or minus - (plus or minus key) puts the number pad into modifier mode.
Die gadget - (up/down arrow keys) Allows you to select the desired die.
Close gadget - Leave the program. Hope it was useful for you!


@endnode

@node code "This is what I did it with..."

CODE

    Dice Calculator was written in JForth Professional, and written using
