contacting Stephen Price one of the address's at the bottom of this doc.


@endnode

@node bugs "Oops..."

BUGS

    The random number generation was psuedo-random only. The seed used, was
exactly the same each time. Fixed that bug by using the MICRO field from
intuition.. That fixed that problem. Thanks to Simon Richards for reporting
that bug.

    Executing the program from a certain screen and then the window is
'Shanghai'ed' to another screen. This may cause the window title bar to cover
part of the window, especially if the two screens use titlebar fonts of
different heights.

    Doesn't work 100% under Workbench 1.3. The help key and the up/down arrow
keys don't do as they should. Also the gadget colours are reversed. I don't
program for 1.3, but it seems I didn't use any 2.0 specific library functions.
(That I noticed..)

@endnode


